[Black "1...e6 - 2...d5 #1"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4
1. e6
2. g3
2. d5
3. Bg2
3. Nf6
4. Nf3{ The advantage of this setup against  e6 - d5  is that we avoid the  Bb4 + Catalan, and remain flexible to decide how to react. }
4. dxc4{ With this move, Black forces White to play his next move, in order to regain the  c4 -pawn. }
5. Qa4+{ The typical way to get back the  c4 -pawn. Now Black has many options. }
5. Bd7( { Not the most played option, but this has become popular in recent years. The two old main moves are }5...Nbd7 { and }5...c6 { , which obviously will be covered in the main course. } )
6. Qxc4
6. c5( 6...Bc6?! { This counters the bishop on  g2  directly. However, White would be better after }7.O-O Nbd7 8.d3 { as Black's minor pieces look uncomfortable in front of his  c7 -pawn. } )
7. Ne5{ We exploit the moment to eye the  d7 -bishop. }
7. Qc8{ Defending the  b7 -pawn. }
8. Nc3( { An alternative development is }8.Nxd7 Qxd7 9.b3 { preparing to fianchetto the  b2 -bishop as well. }9...Nc6 10.Bb2 Be7 11.O-O Rc8 { Both players' setups start taking shape. }12.Rd1 O-O 13.Nc3 a6 { Black prepares to gain space on the queenside. }14.Rac1 { Generally this rook belongs to the semi-open c-file. }14...b5 15.Qf4 { A playable position arose in Nepomniachtchi - Aronian, Paris 2021. } )
8. Nc6
9. Nxd7{ We get the bishop pair. The  c6 -Knight is a great minor piece though. }
9. Qxd7
10. a4{ Even if this is not the main approach, I feel like this is my sort of move, trying to outsmart Black's move order. The idea is to take some space with  a4 - a5  and discourage Black's typical  b7 - b5  expansion. }
10. Be7{ Black's best idea is to continue development. }
11. a5
11. O-O
12. O-O( { The inclusion of }12.a6 b6 { does not lead anywhere at the moment, as Black is solid. We just want our pawn to be on  a5  for the time being. } )
12. Rac8{ Black continues development with this precise move. }
13. d3{ The opening phase is almost done, and it will be analyzed further in the main course. }
