6. Bd6{ Now that  e6 - e5  is harder to achieve, Black has another plan in mind, connected with  Ne4 - f5 , trying to establish a stonewall setup. 6... Bb4  is typical for Catalan-type position, but here we can answer with 7.Nbd2, which doesn't really hurt our plan. The only idea is 7...  Bc3  8.Rb1  e5 . I guess after 9.cxd5  cxd5  10.Qc2!  exd4  11.Bb2  Bxb2  12.Rxb2 White will recollect the  d4  pawn and has a slight edge, at least from a practical point of view. }
7. O-O
