8. Bb2{ Now it's time to develop our Bishop, preparing  Ne5 . }
8. Ne4{ Once again, it seems to me like the only logical follow-up to  Bd6 . }( { If }8...b6 { , we prepare  e4  with }9.Nfd2! Bb7 10.Nc3 { and  e4  is about to be played, with extra power because of the poorly placed  Bd6  . } )
9. Ne5{ White starts to build his  Nd3 - Nf3  scenario. Also,  f3  is an idea at times. }
9. f5
10. e3( { There is no need to rush with, as after }10.f3 Nxe5 11.dxe5 Bc5+ 12.Bd4 dxc4 { unnecessary complications arise. } )
10. Nxe5( { Not necessary, but it's not clear what else to play. The engine suggests }10...a5 { . We can play the elegant }11.f3 { and after }10...Ng5 { the elegant }12.Rf2 { . After }12...a4 { it's }13.Nd3 { and later  Nd2 , preparing  e3 - e4 . I don't think the counterplay connected with the a-pawn is enough for equality for Black. } )( { Something similar happens after the standard }10...Qe7 { - }11.f3 Ng5 12.Rf2 { and next  Nd2  with the idea of  e4 . } )
11. dxe5
11. Be7
12. Nc3
12. Nxc3
