6. c5( { The critical move.    After }6...dxc4?! 7.Qxc4 a6 8.Ne5! b5 9.Qd3 { Black can't play  Bb7 , so White has an edge. } )
7. O-O{ Not losing any time in the center, but continuing the development. }
7. cxd4{ Logically opening the c-file against the  c2 -Queen. }
8. Nxd4
8. e5{ Otherwise it would not make sense to leave the white Knight in the center. }
9. Nf5
9. d4{ Building a dark-squared chain in the center, as the  e7 -bishop will probably be traded. }
10. Bg5{ This is an alternative way to proceed, but as you may guess, I like Bishops! }
10. h6
11. Nxe7+
11. Qxe7
12. Bxf6
12. Qxf6
13. b4{ With a double-edged position. }
