6. c6{ Another version of the slow approach, without going for a quick  c5 . }
7. O-O( { We develop, as }7...dxc4 { would make little sense after }8.Ne5 { . } )
7. Nbd7( { This would be a weird hybrid, as after }8.Qd3 b6 { Black is kind of slow. } )
8. Qd3
8. b6{ Either way, it seems to be an important line from the theoretical point of view. Let's dive into it. }
