10. f5{ Black is trying to prove that the Bishop on  e3  is misplaced. }
11. a3
11. Kh8{ Providing the  g8  square for the  e6  Bishop and avoiding potential tactics on the  a2 - g8  diagonal. }
12. b4{ White doesn't rush with  Na4 , which is also possible. }
12. a6{ An important move for Black, avoiding  b4 - b5 . }
13. Bc5{ Preparing  e2 - e3 , or even  e2 - e4 , killing Black's potential in the center. The  e2 - e4  move has to be played carefully, though, as Black might have the ... Bg4  countermove, winning the battle for the central squares. }
