{ This is another possible reply. Black is basically saying that the move  Bc5  is better with the White's Knight already on  d5 , so it can be exchanged at the right moment. Let's see if it's true. }5. Bc5
6. e3{ We follow with our plan, 'killing' the  c5 -Bishop. }
6. Nxd5{ Probably the best moment to exchange the Knight. }
7. cxd5
7. Ne7{ A safe retreat. }
8. b4{ Not the only way, but it's important to have this little trick in mind. }
8. Bxb4
9. Qg4{ And the  g7 -pawn will taste delicious. }
