5. Bb4{ The Bishop on  b4  together with  f7 - f5  might only have one purpose: fight for the light squares. I don't really believe in this strategy for Black, especially if this involves giving up the Bishop pair. }
6. Nge2{ A more solid choice. }
6. O-O{ This is the most played move. Black simply wants to play  d6  and  Bb4  was meant to bring the Bishop out of the pawn chain. }
