8. a3{ White keeps playing around the bishop on  c5 . As we know,  a2 - a3  is a defensive move, preventing some jump on  b4  in the future. }
8. a5{ Black should probably include this move. }
9. Qc2{ The queen feels safe on  c2  once the pawn is on  a3 . White prepares  Bg5  and long castle! }
9. exd5
10. cxd5
10. c6{ Black follows with their plan of opening up the center. }
11. Bg5{ White threatens  e5 , so there is no time for  cxd5 . }
11. h6{ It is generally useful to include  h7 - h6  against the  Bg5  pin. }( 11...cxd5 12.e5! h6 13.Bh4 g5 14.exf6 gxh4 15.Qf5 { and the Black king feels extremely unsafe. } )
12. Bh4
12. Be7{ Black has to untangle from the pin. }
13. d6{ This is a fascinating line to play. It would be a pity not to mention it. White sacrifices a pawn, to take the initiative. }
13. Bxd6
